{
  "stem": "2522.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "I worked for a consulting firm.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They built the New Jersey Turnpike.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In one of the sweltering summers in 1953, after graduation, in the drafting room, the partner of the consulting firm, Elmer Timby walks by and says, I understand you're going to MIT.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Do you know any statistics?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, of course I know statistics.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He says, well, we have a problem.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We have a dispute on the New Jersey Turnpike.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The toll collectors are going to go on strike, because they think they're overworked.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The government thinks-- the governor thinks that the toll collectors are really featherbedding themselves, because whenever the governor goes to work, there are these guys just sitting at the toll booth doing nothing.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, the governor goes to work at 11 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Obviously, he has a different view than somebody during rush hour.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The consulting firm who built-- the engineering firm who built the New Jersey Turnpike, a construction firm, Howard, Needles, Tammen, and Bergendoff, got the project assignment to figure out whether the toll collectors were overworked or underworked.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so since I was the only guy in the drafting room who claimed that he knew anything about statistics-- which was, as a matter of fact, correct-- got the job of figuring out the overworking of the toll collection personnel.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Turned out that in those days, the New Jersey Turnpike was the only place in the world other than the Bureau of Census that had punch cards which showed when vehicles came on the turnpike and when they got off.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I just said, well send me two months' worth of toll cards for the Jersey Turnpike.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A truck arrived, and I said, how do I get through these cards?",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
